# Rust + Tauri Conventions

- Keep Tauri command functions small and delegate business logic to `services/*`.
- Use `Result<_, String>` at command boundaries with actionable user-facing error text.
- Never introduce non-idempotent DB migrations; schema/index updates must be safe on existing DBs.
- Avoid panics in runtime paths; prefer error propagation and explicit handling.
- Preserve deterministic behavior for tests (stable fixture setup, no hidden randomness in core flows).
- For file operations, avoid destructive behavior unless explicitly requested by user action.
